{"questionId":"27747333","questionHtml":"<p>Find the dimensions of rectangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ORST</mi></math> that has maximum perimeter and determine the value of the maximum perimeter.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>uses the axis of symmetry of a quadratic&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>forms&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>substitutes their value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>so the dimensions of rectangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ORST</mi></math> of maximum perimeter are&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>substitutes their value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>substitutes their values of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp;into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>so the maximum perimeter is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to complete the square&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>M1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>substitutes their value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>so the dimensions of rectangle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ORST</mi></math>&nbsp;of maximum perimeter are&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>so the maximum perimeter is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[6 marks]</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27747333","referenceCode":